.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-5-5::.
6 different games are played: snooker, chess, canasta, bridge, billiard, whist
The people grow 6 different varities of flowers: lily, balloon-flower, aconite, daisy, dahlia, tulip
 1. the person playing bridge is on the left or right of the person who growsballoon-flower##3
 2. the person playing canasta is on the far left or far right##3
 3. the person playing billiard is somewhere to the left of the person who growsdahlia##5
 4. the person who growslily is on the left of the person playing billiard##1
 5. the person who growsdahlia is in an odd position##4
 6. the person who growstulip is the person playing bridge##1
 7. the person playing whist is on the right of the person playing snooker##1
 8. the person playing whist is somewhere to the left of the person playing billiard##5
 9. the person playing billiard is on the left or right of the person playing whist##3
10. the person who growsdaisy is the person playing canasta##1
11. the person playing snooker is in an even position##4
12. the person who growslily is somewhere to the left of the person playing canasta##5

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1    |     2      |     3     |      4      |   5    |     6      |
| Game   | bridge | snooker     | whist    | billiard | chess | canasta    |
| Flower         | tulip  | balloon-flower | lily | aconite     | dahlia | daisy |

